Solus doesn't allow remote ssh connections by default, Ikey thinks it's too risky.
However, we can pull it off with the following command sequence:
	sudo eopkg it openssh-server	#install the host
	sudo systemctl enable sshd	#enable the daemon
	sudo systemctl start sshd	#start the daemon

Be wary, this is fairly risky.
At the same time, 
Malware is for chumps who don't run *nix
